        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Reidsville, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Jericho...
and Prospect Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for north central
North Carolina...and south central and west central Virginia.</instruction>
